					<h2 class="headline" itemprop="headline"><a href="http://monevator.com/weekend-reading-where-are-all-the-billionaires/" rel="bookmark">Weekend reading: Where are all the billionaires?</a></h2>
					<div class="byline small">
						<span class="post_author_intro">by</span> <span class="post_author" itemprop="author">The Investor</span>
						<meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-03-16" />
						<meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2018-03-16" />
						<span class="post_date_intro">on</span> <span class="post_date" title="2018-03-16">March 16, 2018</span>
					</div>
				</div>
				<a class="post_image_link" href="http://monevator.com/weekend-reading-where-are-all-the-billionaires/" title="click to read"><img class="post_image alignright frame" src="http://monevator.monevator.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/weekend-reading.png" alt="Weekend reading: Where are all the billionaires? post image" itemprop="image" /></a>
				<div class="post_content" itemprop="text">
<p><em>What caught my eye this week.</em></p>
<p><span class="drop_cap">H</span>ow many more billionaires would there be if the millionaires of yesteryear had embraced passive investing<sup><a href="#footnote_0_42234" id="identifier_0_42234" class="footnote-link footnote-identifier-link" title="Of course they couldn&rsquo;t, over the time period discussed in the video featured here. Which isn&rsquo;t just pedantry &ndash; it&rsquo;s very possible that making investing easier and cheaper has reduced the expected returns for equities and other assets going forward.">1</a></sup> and saved themselves a bundle?</p>
<p>That&#8217;s the provocative opener in this <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R_7ngg3Jubw&amp;feature=youtu.be" target="_blank" rel="noopener">short video</a> from Robin Powell, the man behind <a href="http://www.evidenceinvestor.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>The Evidence-based Investor</em></a> blog.</p>
<p><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/R_7ngg3Jubw" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>
<p>Robin&#8217;s subject ‚Äì Victor Haghani of fund manager Elm Partners ‚Äì makes plenty of sensible points about keeping costs low and investment aims simple. The video is a nice five-minute introduction to the case for passive investing.</p>
<p>However the <a href="http://monevator.com/consequences-of-income-inequality/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">class warrior in me</a> is rather glad that the super-rich continue to pour billions into expensive <a href="http://www.pionline.com/article/20180119/ONLINE/180119827/hedge-fund-assets-end-2017-at-record-32-trillion-8211-hfr" target="_blank" rel="noopener">hedge funds</a>.</p>
<p>If we&#8217;re to ease wealth inequality, we certainly don&#8217;t want the 1% to care as much as us about getting their fees under 1%!</p>
<p> <a href="http://monevator.com/weekend-reading-where-are-all-the-billionaires/#more-42234" class="more-link">[click to continue&hellip;]</a></p>
<div class="wwsgd" style="display:none;"><p class="alert"><b>Thanks for reading!</b> Monevator is a simply spiffing blog about making, saving, and investing money. Please do check out some of the <a href="http://monevator.com/highlights/" rel="nofollow">best articles</a> or <a href="http://monevator.com/subscribe/" rel="nofollow">follow our posts</a> via Facebook, Twitter, email or RSS.</p></div><ol class="footnotes"><li id="footnote_0_42234" class="footnote">Of course they couldn&#8217;t, over the time period discussed in the video featured here. Which isn&#8217;t just pedantry ‚Äì it&#8217;s very possible that making investing easier and cheaper has reduced the expected returns for equities and other assets going forward. [<a href="#identifier_0_42234" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li></ol>				</div>
